    - "itertools.combinations_with_replacement.__next__.__qualname__ == 'combinations_with_replacement.__next__' (len 38). Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.batched is a C extension type available since Python 3.12. Verified present in Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.batched.__class__.__name__ == 'type' (len 4). Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.batched.__name__ == 'batched' (len 7). Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.batched.__module__ == 'itertools' (len 9). Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "len(itertools.batched.__mro__) == 2 — MRO is [batched, object]. Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.batched.__iter__.__qualname__ == 'batched.__iter__' (len 16). Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.batched.__next__.__qualname__ == 'batched.__next__' (len 16). Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "Both __iter__ and __next__ on these types are wrapper_descriptor objects. Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
